SIMPLE: septillion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Septillion
<hw>Sep*til"lion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>septilion</ets>, formed fr. L. <ets>septem</ets> seven, in
imitation of <ets>million</ets>.]</ety> <def>According to the French
method of numeration (which is followed also in the United States), the
number expressed by a unit with twenty-four ciphers annexed. According
to the English method, the number expressed by a unit with forty-two
ciphers annexed. See <er>Numeration</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Septimole</ent>⟦br⟧
